A wannan Asabar, birnin New York zai karbi bakuncin bikin Global Citizen, wani biki na shekara-shekara na kiɗa da ke da manyan taurari da kuma manufa mai ban sha'awa kamar kawo ƙarshen talauci a duniya.
A shekara ta bakwai a jere, bikin Global Citizen zai tara dubban mutane a Central Park don su ji dadin ba kawai yin wasan kwaikwayon taurari ba, kamar Janet Jackson, Cardi B da Shawn Mendes, amma kuma su kara wayar da kan jama'a game da ainihin burin taron, kawar da matsanancin talauci ta 2030.
Bikin Global Citizen, wanda aka fara a shekarar 2012, wani ci gaba ne na Global Poverty Project, wata kungiya ta kasa da kasa da ke fatan kawo karshen talauci ta hanyar kara yawan mutanen da ke fafutukar yaki da talauci.
Don samun tikiti kyauta (sai dai idan sun kasance a shirye su biya tikitin VIP), masu halartar wasan kwaikwayon dole ne su yi ayyuka da yawa kamar aikin sa kai, aika imel ga shugaban duniya, kiran waya, ko kuma duk wata hanya mai ma'ana don wayar da kan jama'a game da burin su na kawar da talauci.
Amma, yaya nasarar da Global Citizen ya samu, idan aka yi la'akari da cewa yana da shekaru 12 da ya rage ya cim ma burinsa?
Shin ra'ayin bayar da kyauta ta hanyar yin wasa kyauta hanya ce ta tabbatar wa mutane cewa suna bukatar kira zuwa aiki, ko kuwa wani yanayi ne na abin da ake kira "clicktivism" inda mutane ke jin cewa ta hanyar sanya hannu kan takarda ta yanar gizo ko kuma aika tweets suna kawo canji?
Tun daga shekarar 2011, Global Citizen ta ce ta samu fiye da mutane miliyan 19 da suka yi amfani da wannan shafin wajen neman cimma burin.
Ya ce, wannan ya sa shugabannin duniya su sanar da alkawura da manufofi da za su kai fiye da dala biliyan 37 da za su shafi rayukan mutane biliyan 2.25 a shekara ta 2030.
